# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# 
# <body>
# 
# <footer>
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, no logic change)
#   refactor - Code refactoring
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks (deps, config, etc.)
#
# Scope (optional): inventory, receiving, admin, auth, receiving, etc.
#
# Examples:
#   feat(inventory): Add lot lifecycle sheet component
#   fix(auth): Resolve password reset issue
#   refactor(actions): Consolidate inventory actions
#   chore(deps): Update Prisma to 6.19.0
#
# Body should explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# Footer can reference issues: Fixes #123, Closes #456


